Advanced Performance Metrics and Attribution
Modern targeted lead generation requires sophisticated attribution understanding how different touchpoints contribute to eventual customer outcomes. First-click attribution gives credit to initial lead source but ignores subsequent influences. Last-click attribution credits final touchpoint before conversion but undervalues earlier awareness activities.

Progressive organizations implement multi-touch attribution models—either time-decay models giving more weight to recent interactions while acknowledging earlier contributions, algorithmic models using machine learning to model actual conversion drivers, or custom models reflecting your specific sales process.

For targeted lead generation specifically, implement attribution models that properly credit initial engagement for launching customer journeys. A cold outreach email that opens a conversation, leading to nurture, leading to eventual customer, should credit that initial outreach with significant conversion contribution even if someone else closes the deal months later.

